chrome_history

Top-Level Variables
history: ChromeHistory
Classes
ChromeHistory

Use the chrome.history API to interact with the browser's record of visited pages. You can add, remove, and query for URLs in the browser's history. To override the history page with your own version, see [Override Pages](override.html).

Top-Level Variables

static final ChromeHistory history

Fields

final Stream onVisitRemoved
final Stream onVisited

Getters and Setters

Stream<dynamic> get onVisitRemoved

Fired when one or more URLs are removed from the history service. When all visits have been removed the URL is purged from history.

Stream<dynamic> get onVisited

Fired when a URL is visited, providing the HistoryItem data for that URL. This event fires before the page has loaded.

Methods

void addUrl(dynamic details, dynamic callback)

Adds a URL to the history at the current time with a [transition type](#transition_types) of "link".

void deleteAll(dynamic callback)

Deletes all items from the history.

void deleteRange(dynamic range, dynamic callback)

Removes all items within the specified date range from the history. Pages will not be removed from the history unless all visits fall within the range.

void deleteUrl(dynamic details, dynamic callback)

Removes all occurrences of the given URL from the history.

void getVisits(dynamic details, dynamic callback)

Retrieves information about visits to a URL.

void search(dynamic query, dynamic callback)

Searches the history for the last visit time of each page matching the query.
